# Node + Python Symmetry (cli-js / cli-py)

When you change one CLI (Node or Python), **update the other to match**.

## Scope

- **packages/cli-js**: TypeScript CLI (init, doctor, plan, implement, config, install).
- **packages/cli-py**: Python CLI with the same commands and semantics under `planforge/`.

Corresponding areas:

| Node (cli-js)              | Python (cli-py)                |
|----------------------------|---------------------------------|
| src/commands/*.ts          | planforge/commands/*.py        |
| src/providers/claude.ts, codex.ts | planforge/providers/claude.py, codex.py |
| src/utils/shell.ts, paths.ts     | planforge/utils/shell.py, paths.py     |
| src/templates/install.ts   | planforge/templates/install.py  |
| src/config/*.ts            | planforge config (if present)   |

## What to mirror

- **New command or subcommand** → add to both `index.ts` (Node) and `cli.py` (Python).
- **Change in command behavior** (e.g. init flow, doctor checks, plan/implement options) → same UX and semantics in both.
- **Provider API or check** (e.g. runPlan, runImplement, path resolution) → same logic in both codebases.
- **Config / presets** (planforge.json, getPresetForProviders) → keep behavior aligned; Python may call Node or reimplement the same rules.

## Checklist

- [ ] After editing a command or provider in **cli-js**, update the corresponding file in **cli-py** (and vice versa).
- [ ] CLI surface (subcommands, flags, exit codes, messages) stays consistent between `planforge` (Node) and `planforge` (Python).
